2016 WW44 Purley-FPGA Server SKX/LBG B-Stepping BKC Release Announcement (BKC #3)

\n \n \n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\n \n
\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2016 WW44 Purley-FPGA Server SKX/LBG B-Stepping BKC release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\n \n Linux\n server. The auto-installer packages are available on the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Bei, Ling.

Test Result:

\xc2\xb7       Finish\nBKC test execution on RHEL 7.2. Please visit HPQC for test details

\xc2\xb7       Purley FPGA (RP Board: Neon City FPGA)

o    Total test cases: 56 ;\nPassed test cases is 50 and pass rate is 89%.\nThe full validation result can be found in OSS

o    Test coverage:  SKX-FPGA B0 ES2/LBG B1: Run P1 & P2 BKC\ntest cases.

 

Sighting Update:

\xc2\xb7       Key\nSightings:

o    [2016_WW43\nBKC][BIOS:105_D11][Neon city FPGA] Cannot enter OS after enable VT-d in BIOS 5345474

\xc3\xbc  With this week\xe2\x80\x99s IFWI, the fail rate is\ngetting much improved. And it no longer blocks other testing or BKC release

\xc2\xb7       Open\nSighting details can be found here; Full sighting list can\nbe found in\nHSD

 

SW&HW Configurations:

\xc2\xb7       Changed to SKX-FPGA B0\nES2

\xc2\xb7      \nSW and IFWI changes can be found here ; HW configuration can\nbe found here

\xc2\xb7      \n  WA/HW Reword can be\nfound here

 


P&P Update:

1. Run NLB with Linux kernel 4.7.0, other tests are running with Linux Kernel 3.10.0

2. Remove specpower test from our plan,because FPGA don\'t use specpower, and focus on Idle power and NLB loading power test. 

3. Changed CPU from QL66/QL67 to QLGZ(ES2) for power and performance test

4. Linpack score has around 10% drop, after cross check, this is cause by CPU changed.
